== Text Effect
---------------

    CSS3 contains several new functionalities tha t web  developers and desogniers can use
    to style alter,transform customize and enhance text. the result of all these new finctionalities is that the need to images to achieve
    desired text effect is nicely reduced.\

    css3 contains several new text features.

    the following are the properties in css3 that can be utilized to add impact to text:
            1. Text-shadow
            2. word-wrap
            3. word-break
            4. text-overflow
            
1. Text-shadow

<style>
    h1{
    text-shadow: 5px 5px 5px  #ff0000;
    }
</style>
------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. word-wrap

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Word wrap</title>
    </head>
    <style type="text/css">
        p.test{
            width: 12em;
            border: 3px solid red;
            word-wrap: break-word;
        }
    </style>
    <body>
        <p class="test">This paragraph contains a very long word:
            thosisverylongwordsnaggodword the long word will break and wrap to next line
        </p>
    </body>
</html>
------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. word-break
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      p.N1 {
        width: 150px;
        border: 2px solid red;
        word-break: break-all;
        text-align: left;
        font-size: 20px;
      }
      p.N2 {
        width: 140px;
        border: 2px solid blueviolet;
        word-break: keep-all;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body style="text-align: center">
    <p class="N1">
      CSS3 referes to cascading style sheet level 3 which at time of writtng is
      under development by W3C.
    </p>
    <p class="N2">
      CSS3 referes to cascading style sheet level 3 which at time of writtng is
      under development by W3C.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

4. text-overflow
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>text-overflow</title>
  </head>
  <style>
    p.N1 {
      white-space: nowrap; /*Text not goes to next line */
      width: 200px;
      border: 1px solid dodgerblue;
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: clip;
    }
    p.N2 {
      white-space: nowrap;
      width: 200px;
      border: 1px solid #631ee2;
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
    }
  </style>
  <body>
    <h2>Text-Overflow</h2>
    <p class="N1">
      Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Magnam illo
      recusandae porro. Eligendi, itaque accusamus! Nobis dolorem a nam
      accusamus debitis quidem. Dolores repudiandae fugit expedita ratione quis
      deserunt delectus.
    </p>

    <h2>text-overflow:ellipsis</h2>
    <p class="N2">
      Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Temporibus,
      sequi. Magnam alias totam rem nulla suscipit, quibusdam excepturi tempore
      delectus similique corporis voluptates possimus vero dolorum
      exercitationem esse eum sunt?
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
