colors
------------
    --------------------------------------------
    -rgba()
     h1{
            color: rgba(0, 0, 255, 0.5);
           }
           p{
            background-color: blueviolet;
           }
        </style>
    -------------------------------------------
    hsl()
     <style>
          h1{
            color: hsla(360, 80%,50%, 0.5);
          }
          p{
            background-color: hsl(30, 10%, 50%);
          }
        </style>
    
    ---------------------------------------------    
    hsla()
        <style>
          h1{
            color: hsla(360, 80%,50%, 0.5);
          }
          p{
            background-color: hsl(30, 10%, 50%);
          }
        </style>
    --------------------------------------------- 
=========================================================

The OPACITY PRoperty
--------------------
    Aplha transperency is not only way of making transparent element;
    an alternative approach is to use opacity property.

    it works in similar to way to the alpha channel in RGBA or HSLA by taking a value between 0 and 1 the difference being that the only value specified for the property.This means we still need to declare the color using another property such as background-color or coloe.

    to set an article background to be 50% opaque, we would use.

    article{
        background-color:#fff;
    } opacity:0.5;

ex:
    <style>
        img{
            opacity: 0.5;
        }
        p{
            opacity: 0.7;
            filter: Alpha(opacity=50);
        }
    </style>

